<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="248" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="37.[136,1451,1598,1769]" box="[136,547,1598,1624]" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,292,1598,1624]" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[471,543,1598,1624]" name="Brazil" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[136,1451,1598,1769]" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1634,1660]" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">Notes:—</emphasis>
Like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey &amp; Sanson" authorityYear="2006" box="[354,571,1635,1660]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="248" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conceicionensis">
<emphasis box="[354,571,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">M. conceicionensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barb. Rodr." box="[587,784,1634,1660]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="248" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lonchophyllus">
<emphasis box="[587,784,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">M. lonchophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[843,992,1635,1660]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="248" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis box="[843,992,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">M. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species is endemic to southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[136,204,1670,1696]" name="Brazil" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and has a dark red to purple-spotted perianth, lip base with a small auricle on both sides and margins revolute to the apex and the characteristic fimbriate anther cap. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fraga &amp; Kollmann" authorityYear="2003" box="[880,997,1706,1732]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="37" pageNumber="248" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruschii">
<emphasis box="[880,997,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">M. ruschii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily recognized among these by its elliptic to ovate petals 
<emphasis box="[390,413,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="248">vs</emphasis>
. ovate at the base then narrow with revolute margins forming rounded linear petals.
</paragraph>
